A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Part 4 of Article 6 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia
2 Annotated, relating to financing under the "Quality Basic Education Act," so as to revise
3 QBE program weights based on recommendations of the 2015 Education Reform
4 Commission; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
5 purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Part 4 of Article 6 of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
9 relating to financing under the "Quality Basic Education Act," is amended by revising Code
10 Section 20-2-161, relating to the Quality Basic Education Formula, as follows:
11 "20-2-161.
12 (a) The high middle school general education program is declared to be the base program
13 against which the cost of all other instructional programs shall be compared. The amount
14 of funds needed by each full-time equivalent student in the base program, in order that such
15 program can be sufficiently funded to provide quality basic education to all enrolled
16 students, shall be known as the 'base amount' and shall reflect program components which
